description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Are you experienced in providing Complex Care to children and young people?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare are seeking experienced Health Care Assistants to support a young boy with complex care needs at his home in Wolverhampton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dedicated and compassionate Health Care Assistants who are passionate about their job, enjoy delivering one to one support and who can build positive relationships with our service users and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service user is a lovely young boy who lives with his family in Wolverhampton.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;He really enjoys watching lifts and escalators and can spend hours watching videos of different types and naming the countries they are in. He also enjoys trips out to the local shopping center to see them in action.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is important for his care team to encourage independence as much as possible as he likes his own space and does not like to be mothered. He can become frustrated if he is not able to do things that his peers are able to.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Routine is also very important to him and he likes things set in a certain way.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our ideal applicant will be calm, patient and ideally have knowledge of Autism, although this is not essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 months previous care experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medication Administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Moving and Handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Epilepsy and seizure management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Autism&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge of Cerebral Palsy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Saturday 12pm - 5pm&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on his day to day life.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why work for Apollo Home Healthcare?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We specialise in the provision of highly complex clinical care services delivered in the homes of service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are passionate about delivering the highest standard of care and we recognise that our Nurses, Healthcare Assistants and Support Workers are integral to doing this. In return for your hard work and dedication you will receive:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Flexible hours to suit&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Confirmed rotas&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent rates of pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Holiday pay&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full clinical training&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to work with other service users in the area&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ongoing professional training and development&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We need key workers on the front line supporting our service users in the fight against the COVID-19 Pandemic. Please do not hesitate to contact our dedicated recruitment team on 01902 847111 or email onrecruitment@apollohomehealthcare.comto find out more.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you looking to expand your skills and enhance your career to include providing Complex Clinical Care or do you already have Complex Care experience?&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Apollo Home Healthcare is seeking experienced Healthcare Assistants to support a lady with complex care needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for dedicated and compassionate Healthcare Assistants who are passionate about their job, enjoy delivering one to one support and who can build positive relationships with our service users and their families.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service user is in her early 20&#39;s and lives with her family in Stoke-on-Trent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;She requires a team of experienced Healthcare Assistants to provide care throughout both the day and night.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be supporting with her social, personal care needs, medication administration, moving and handling and carrying out clinical interventions as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are committed, motivated, enjoy delivering one to one support and can build positive relationships with our service users and their families, this could be just the position you are looking for!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Essential Experience Required&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;6 months previous care experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Medication Administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Personal Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Moving and Handling&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Desirable Experience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respiratory Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Seizure Management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oral Suction&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Nebuliser Care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enteral Feed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We have the following shifts available;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full Time Days&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Full Time Nights&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;This is a personally rewarding role where you can build on your clinical skills and experience, whilst delivering exceptional care and support to our service user and really making an impact on her day to day life.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
